          "name": "run_cli_command",
          "response": {
            "result": "{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"phase_completed\": \"PLANNING\",\n  \"product_spec_hash\": \"c4c04323\",\n  \"identified_modules\": [\n    \"ui-gateway\",\n    \"logic-api\",\n    \"data-store\"\n  ],\n  \"task_id\": \"EPIC-DFP\",\n  \"module_id\": \"SYSTEM\"\n}# Product Specification: Dimensional Factor Pulse (DFP)\n\n## 1. System Overview\nThe Dimensional Factor Pulse (DFP) is a containerized financial dashboard designed to visualize the performance premiums of Dimensional Fund Advisors (DFA) proxy funds against their standard market benchmarks. The system is a 3-tier architecture (UI, API, Data) orchestrated via Docker Compose, demonstrating automated provisioning, data fetching, and interactive visualization.\n\n## 2. Architecture & Modules\n\n### 2.1 UI Gateway (`ui-gateway`)\n- **Stack**: React/Vite, Tailwind CSS, Nginx.\n- **Package Manager**: `pnpm`.\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  - Serve the frontend application.\n  - Reverse proxy `/api/*` requests to the `logic-api` backend at `http://logic-api:8001/*` via a custom `nginx.conf`.\n  - Expose host port `8000` mapping to container port `80`.\n- **UI Components**:\n  - **Header/Title**: \"Dimensional Factor Pulse\".\n  - **Heatmap Visualization**: Use `@nivo/heatmap` (or `apexcharts`) to render a grid-based heatmap.\n    - **X-axis**: Date.\n    - **Y-axis**: Funds (Proxy Pairs).\n    - **Color Scale**: Diverging color scale indicating positive (e.g., green) or negative (e.g., red) premiums.\n    - **Interactivity**: Tooltip on hover displaying Date, Premium Value (to 4 decimal places), Region, and Proxy Pair.\n  - **Dynamic Controls**:\n    - **Fund Selector**: Dropdown to select a specific proxy pair (US Core Equity, Intl. Vector, Emerging Markets) or view all.\n    - **Timeframe Toggle**: Buttons for 1D, 5D, 1M, 6M, 1Y, YTD.\n  - **Footer**: \"Built by SDLC-Factory\" with automated `GIT_COMMIT_HASH` and `BUILD_DATE`.\n- **Testing**: Include Playwright as a dev dependency for E2E testing.\n\n### 2.2 Logic API (`logic-api`)\n- **Stack**: Python, `uv` (pyproject.toml), FastAPI (or similar framework).\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  - Serve REST API on internal port `8001` (mapped to host `8001`).\n  - Calculate daily premiums: `Premium = DFA Proxy Return - Benchmark Return`.\n  - Store and return all calculations to 4 decimal places.\n  - Fetch historical data using `yfinance` for the last 730 days on first boot.\n  - Provide a `/health` endpoint to verify API and Database connectivity.\n- **Endpoints**:\n  - `GET /api/heatmap`: Accepts `fund_id` (optional, for filtering) and `timeframe`. Returns a pre-calculated JSON structure formatted specifically for `@nivo/heatmap` (array of objects with `id` as fund name and `data` as array of `{x: date, y: premium}`).\n- **Resilience**:\n  - Startup script MUST implement an explicit polling loop (e.g., using `tenacity` or a custom while loop) to attempt Postgres connection every 2 seconds (up to 10 attempts) before seeding data or binding the port.\n\n### 2.3 Data Store (`data-store`)\n- **Stack**: PostgreSQL.\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  - Persist daily adjusted market closes and calculated premiums for the supported funds and benchmarks.\n  - Isolated from the host machine (no host port mapping, internal Docker network only).\n  - Data persistence via Docker volumes.\n\n## 3. Business Logic & Data Dictionary\n\n### 3.1 Proxy Pairs\n| Region | DFA Proxy Ticker | Benchmark Ticker |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **US Core Equity** | `DFAC` | `^GSPC` (S&P 500) |\n| **Intl. Vector** | `DXIV` | `URTH` (MSCI World ex US) |\n| **Emerging Markets** | `DFAE` | `EEM` (MSCI EM Index) |\n\n### 3.2 Premium Calculation\n- **Daily Return**: `(Price_Today - Price_Yesterday) / Price_Yesterday`\n- **Premium**: `DFA_Daily_Return - Benchmark_Daily_Return`\n- **Precision**: 4 decimal places.\n\n## 4. Non-Functional Requirements\n- **Authentication**: None. The system is fully open for demonstration purposes.\n- **Containerization**: All modules must be Dockerized and orchestrated via `docker-compose.yml`.\n- **Zero-Touch Provisioning**: The system must build, seed data, and serve the UI without manual intervention.\n"
          }
        },
