        "function_call": {
          "id": null,
          "args": {
            "command": "cat << 'EOF' > docs/API_CONTRACTS.md\n# API Contracts\n\n## > BEGIN_ENVIRONMENT\n- **Stack**: Docker Compose (React/Vite/Nginx, Python/FastAPI, PostgreSQL)\n- **Entry_Point**: `http://localhost:8000` (UI) and `http://localhost:8001` (API)\n- **Interface_Mount_Selector**: `#root`\n- **INTEGRATION_TEST_CMD**: `cd ui-gateway && CI=true npx playwright test --reporter=list`\n## > END_ENVIRONMENT\n\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: ui-gateway\n- **Type**: ORCHESTRATOR\n- **Description**: The frontend application, Nginx reverse proxy, and global Docker Compose orchestrator.\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  - Write `docker-compose.yml` at the project root to orchestrate `ui-gateway`, `logic-api`, and `data-store`.\n  - Map host port `8000` to container port `80` for the UI.\n  - Map host port `8001` to container port `8001` for the API.\n  - Configure Nginx to serve the React/Vite build and reverse proxy `/api/` to `http://logic-api:8001/api/`.\n  - Implement the React UI with Tailwind CSS.\n  - UI Components:\n    - Header: \"Dimensional Factor Pulse\".\n    - Heatmap: `@nivo/heatmap` or `apexcharts`. X-axis: Date, Y-axis: Funds. Diverging color scale. Tooltip with Date, Premium Value (4 decimal places), Region, Proxy Pair.\n    - Controls: Fund Selector dropdown (US Core Equity, Intl. Vector, Emerging Markets, All), Timeframe Toggle (1D, 5D, 1M, 6M, 1Y, YTD).\n    - Footer: \"Built by SDLC-Factory\" with `GIT_COMMIT_HASH` and `BUILD_DATE`.\n  - E2E Testing: Playwright tests in `ui-gateway/tests/` to verify UI rendering and API integration.\n- **Routing Contract**:\n  - Nginx routes `^/api/(.*)$` to `http://logic-api:8001/api/$1`.\n  - Docker Compose defines services: `ui-gateway` (builds from `./ui-gateway`), `logic-api` (builds from `./logic-api`), `data-store` (image `postgres:15-alpine`, uses `data-store/init.sql`).\n## > END_MODULE\n\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: logic-api\n- **Type**: LEAF\n- **Description**: Python FastAPI backend for data fetching, calculation, and serving.\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  - Serve REST API on port `8001`.\n  - Fetch historical data (last 730 days) via `yfinance` on first boot for pairs: DFAC/^GSPC, DXIV/URTH, DFAE/EEM.\n  - Calculate daily premiums: `(DFA_Daily_Return - Benchmark_Daily_Return)` to 4 decimal places.\n  - Store data in PostgreSQL.\n  - Implement explicit polling loop (e.g., `tenacity`) to attempt Postgres connection every 2 seconds (up to 10 attempts) before seeding data or binding the port.\n- **Endpoints**:\n  - `GET /health`: Returns strict JSON:\n    ```json\n    {\n      \"status\": \"string\",\n      \"db_connected\": \"boolean\"\n    }\n    ```\n  - `GET /api/heatmap`: Accepts query params `fund_id` (optional string) and `timeframe` (string). Returns strict JSON:\n    ```json\n    [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"string\",\n        \"data\": [\n          {\n            \"x\": \"string\",\n            \"y\": \"number\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n    ```\n## > END_MODULE\n\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: data-store\n- **Type**: LEAF\n- **Description**: PostgreSQL database schema initialization.\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  - Create `data-store/init.sql` to define the schema.\n  - Schema must include tables for storing daily prices, returns, and calculated premiums for the proxy pairs.\n  - Ensure the schema supports the queries required by `logic-api`.\n  - No host port mapping; internal Docker network only.\n  - Data persistence via Docker volumes.\n## > END_MODULE\nEOF\n",
            "cwd": "/home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP"
          },
